-- Allergan CEO resigns from Edwards Lifesciences' board
-- By Shailesh Kuber in Bangalore
-- Fri Oct 03, 2014 05:00PM EDT
-- None



Oct 3 (Reuters) - Edwards Lifesciences Corp <EW.N> said David Pyott resigned from the medical device maker's board to devote more time to his role as chairman and CEO of Allergan Inc <AGN.N>.

The resignation of Pyott, who joined Edwards' board in 2000, is effective immediately, the company said in a statement. [ID:nPn4lTVH7] Allergan is fighting a $53.7-billion hostile bid from Canada's Valeant Pharmaceuticals International Inc <VRX.TO> and billionaire William Ackman's Pershing Square. [ID:nL2N0RS0IP]